headline: Rollins (ROL) Valuation Check As Long Term Returns Contrast With A High P/E Multiple
summary: Rollins (ROL) is back on investors’ radar after recent trading left the stock modestly weaker over the past month, while it has still shown positive moves year to date and over the past year. See our latest analysis for Rollins. The recent 1 day share price return of 1.89% to US$60.89 comes after a softer 30 day share price return of a 3.87% decline. Longer term total shareholder returns of 17.61% over one year and 96.99% over five years suggest the broader trend has remained supportive even...
